rComments: This class is poorly taught. All notes are posted online and lecture is quite boring. She teaches directly off slides which often contained mistakes. Last year, she cancelled lecture the day of an exam to protest so she could get a contract. Always make sure to attend discussion though. TA's are your friends if you want to pass this class easily.
Never again... Super hard class for freshman level
Hard grader. Expect difficult exams.

Lena's voice can get annoying but if you actually get yourself to pay attention you'll do well. All the notes and examples are online so it is relatively easy to do the homework. Also she posts previous midterms online so you know what to expect but there is nothing for the final so expect to study a ton for it.

Her voice is very boring, but if you pay attention to her lectures (that she posts online) she says exactly what you need for the tests. She doesn't teach you anything you don't need and gets right to the point. If you ask for it, she will help you with anything you need. She wants everyone to pass the tests, which are super hard.
I took her Math125 last semester. She is cute and helpful and she puts all the notes online, so you do not have to go to her class... lol

Do not take her class. She goes way too fast, Its insane. Her class and teaching sucks.  Her handwriting is awful, and she teaches us things that we don't even need to be learning, wasting our time. She does give extra credit, but the class is tough. She's a horrible teacher and does not know how to explain anything.

I found the textbook to be much more helpful than Lena - I stopped going to lecture after the first two weeks and studied only out of the book.  Other than that, her lectures are pretty much torture from what I remember but it was definitely not difficult material if you put time in to reading the book.
Worst class ever

Avoid this class if possible. If you're trying to get into business, there are easier courses to take that won't destroy your GPA. There's homework due every Friday. She only curves tests if the class average is under 75% (it almost never is). Worst class ever. She's a good person, but a terrible teacher.
Writes at the speed of light

Extremely hard class. She goes way too fast! It's ridiculous! The homework is really hard as well and it does not even prepare you well for the test. If your smart with math take the class but if not beware!

Do NOT take this class with this teacher if you don't have to. She is unclear and you can barely read her notes. She has awful handwriting and her voice is quiet and not understandable. There is only one homework assignment each week, but you don't know how to do any of it because she is so awful at explaining everything. I would not recommend.
She moves way too fast and never explains WHY she is doing something. Incredibly unclear and hard to follow.

Even though classes are optional and videos and notes are posted online, don't skip unless necessary. The lectures are not fun in person, but trying to watch them on YouTube instead is impossible. To her credit, the notes are very easy to follow--she uses different colors to help illustrate where things come from. Tests are manageable and curved.
You will get an easy A if you pay attention to her. Although sometimes she is not very clear but mostly she is very helpful.
Best math teacher in my life. Super Cute and friendly! You'll be fine as long as you read the lecture notes and do the homework

She's soooo sweet and cute; very good at teaching. Midterms can be challenging at times but she'll give curves. She puts all the lecture notesvideos online so that you can check them whenever you want. Her lecture notes are the best I've seen----clear and very useful. DON'T  buy the textbook, you'll never use it.
She's tough and her exams are extremely hard.  If you can take this class at a community college, take it! I warned you.

Sweet lady, but the nature of this class makes it difficult to teach. She does a good job of integrating math and business concepts, and is able to cover a lot of material in the semester. Starts with the basics. Not too difficult if you put in the effort, but you have to stay on top of homework and discussion quizzes. She's strict but nice.
